The basic unit of budget management,
 can be an organization or a cost center.
page.budget.modal.tooltip.control:
Budget control methods are Not control, Full control, On schedule and Accumulative.
Not control means, the current budget is not required to have control
Full control means, the total budget will be used during the whole period
On schedule means, the budget for each period is limited to only current period use
Accumulative means, the usage of current period budget is not limited on current period, it also could use budget from previous period

page.rule.settings.modal.expired.detail:
Current year expiration date: is the set date from next year. the default time is 0:00 1st January from next year
 If this holiday type is only valid for current year, please set 1st January for expiration date. After 1st January next year, the holiday for current year is unavailable 
 If it sets 1st March as expiration date, the holiday could be valid until the end of February next year 
 Notice: It will be changed immediately by expiration date modification. So that it recommends to modify on next year if previous years’ holiday would not like to be affected by current expiration date modification.
 
  Examples:
If changing the expiration date from 1st March to 1st February on January 2017, then the last of holiday for 2016 is not available to use from the start of February 
 If changing the expiration date from 1st March to 1st February on April 2017, the last of holiday for 2016 is still not available due to it has been due and the new setting will be valid for 2017 holiday 
 If changing the expiration date from 1st March to 1st June on April 2017, the last of holiday for 2016 is not available before modification. After modification, it is available before the end of June.
